org.jgentleframework.services.objectpooling
Interface Pool

All Known Subinterfaces:
BasePooling
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractBaseController, AbstractBaseFactory, AbstractBasePooling, CommonPool, StackPool, WeakPool
public interface Pool

A pooling interface.

Pool defines a trivially simple pooling interface.

Author:
Quoc Chung - mailto: skydunkpro@yahoo.com

Method Detail

addObject

void addObject()
               throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException,
                      java.lang.Throwable
Creates an object using the implementation dependent mechanism, passivate it, and then place it in the idle object pool. addObject is useful for "pre-loading" a pool with idle objects. (Optional operation).

Throws:
java.lang.Throwable - when creation fails.
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - when this pool cannot add new idle objects.

clear

void clear()
           throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException,
                  java.lang.Throwable
Clears any objects sitting idle in the pool, releasing any associated resources (optional operation). Idle objects cleared must be destroyed.

Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this implementation does not support the operation
java.lang.Throwable

close

void close()
           throws java.lang.Throwable
Close this pool, and free any resources associated with it.

Throws:
java.lang.Throwable - implementations should silently fail if not all resources can be freed.

getNumActive

int getNumActive()
                 throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
Returns the number of instances currently borrowed from this pool (optional operation). Returns a negative value if this information is not available.

Returns:
the number of instances currently borrowed from this pool or a negative value if unsupported
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this implementation does not support the operation

getNumIdle

int getNumIdle()
               throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
Returns the number of instances currently idle in this pool (optional operation). This may be considered an approximation of the number of objects that can be borrowed without creating any new instances. Returns a negative value if this information is not available.

Returns:
the number of instances currently idle in this pool or a negative value if unsupported
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this implementation does not support the operation

invalidateObject

void invalidateObject(java.lang.Object obj)
                      throws java.lang.Throwable
Invalidates an object from the pool.

This method should be used when an object that has been borrowed is determined (due to an exception or other problem) to be invalid.

Parameters:
obj - a borrowed instance to be disposed.
Throws:
java.lang.Throwable - the throwable

isEmpty

boolean isEmpty()
Checks if this pool is empty.

Returns:
true, if is empty

obtainObject

java.lang.Object obtainObject()
                              throws java.util.NoSuchElementException,
                                     java.lang.Throwable
Obtains an instance from this pool.

The behaviour of this method when the pool has been exhausted is not strictly specified (although it may be specified by implementations). This method will return null to indicate exhaustion or throw a NoSuchElementException.

Returns:
an instance from this pool.
Throws:
java.util.NoSuchElementException - when the pool is exhausted and cannot or will not return another instance.
java.lang.Throwable
